Package jetbrains.mps.openapi.navigation

Class NavigationSupport

  • java.lang.Object
    • jetbrains.mps.openapi.navigation.NavigationSupport
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    jetbrains.mps.components.CoreComponent
    public abstract class NavigationSupport
extends Object
implements jetbrains.mps.components.CoreComponent
    Facility to reveal different aspects of an mps project, either in a project tree or in an editor. This is low-level, implementation API and shall not be used unless there's justification to do so (e.g. you've got an SNode and need to do something with an Editor from openNode(Project, SNode, boolean, boolean). Otherwise, use EditorNavigator or ProjectPaneNavigator FIXME it's odd to require external methods to wrap into read/write/EDT if we can do it ourselves here (with project and its model access available) FIXME it's odd this class lives in [editor-api], why not in platform/ui?

        public abstract Editor openNode​(@NotNull
                                jetbrains.mps.project.Project mpsProject,
                                @NotNull
                                org.jetbrains.mps.openapi.model.SNode node,
                                boolean focus,
                                boolean select)
        Opens node in the editor. Requires: model read, EDT. Unless you care about return value or do some extra stuff with the node, use EditorNavigator.open(SNodeReference) instead
        Parameters:
        mpsProject - project where node is looked up and where editor is opened
        node - alive node from model repository
        focus - move focus if needed - to editor or to inspector
        select - select node (or its parent) in editor and inspector (if exist)
